If X is indeed running on the affected monitor, and you can get remote
authority to write to the X server driving your VGA port, you might be able
to control the output using "xrandr". It might also be possible to specify
an xrandr command line for the display manager's benefit.

X.org configuration has gone largely automatic, but it should still be
possible to constrain the monitor settings without going full-tilt into
CRTC timings...
